The paper deals with the automatic detection of neurons in histological images of the human brain using anisotropic diffusion and partial differential equations. This involves image processing and computer vision techniques, which are typically covered in the computer vision (cs.CV) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. The paper also discusses parameter optimization, which falls under the machine learning (cs.LG) sub-category. The use of anisotropic diffusion and partial differential equations also suggests a connection to the neural networks and deep learning (cs.NE) sub-category. Finally, the paper involves image analysis and information retrieval, which are relevant to the information retrieval (cs.IR) sub-category.
